                            <comment id="15003480" author="githubbot" created="Fri, 13 Nov 2015 03:17:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user bgould opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/691&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/691&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3417&quot; title=&quot;&amp;quot;namespace xsd&amp;quot; is not really working&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-3417&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-3417&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;namespace xsd&quot; is not really working&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Added support for annotations on namespaces in IDL.  This allows for specifying a namespace uri like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    `namespace xsd test (uri = &apos;http://my.example.com/&apos;)`&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Updated XSD generator to take advantage of this new feature in order to generate namespace URIs based off of the annotation, unless no annotation is present - in which case the fallback behavior is to use the value of `program_-&amp;gt;get_namespace(&quot;xsd&quot;)` as it was previously.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can merge this pull request into a Git repository by running:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    $ git pull &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/bgould/thrift&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/bgould/thrift&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3417&quot; title=&quot;&amp;quot;namespace xsd&amp;quot; is not really working&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-3417&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-3417&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

